- The integer array parameter `nums` must have a length greater than or equal to 3 and less than or equal to 10000.
- All values in the integer array parameter `nums` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 1000000.
- The integer result is the largest perimeter of a triangle with a non-zero area formed from three lengths in the integer array parameter `nums`.
- If it is impossible to form any triangle of a non-zero area, the integer result is equal to 0.